On Monday, March 24, 2003, at 01:33 PM, Alessandro Baretta wrote:

> If I use ocamlcp to attempt to profile the execution of a caml program 
> with classes, I get a syntax error. This is the piece of code 
> generated by ocamlcp where the syntax error comes up:
>
> class environment (env:env) = object
>   (__ocaml_prof_cnt_xcaml_session_.(5) <- Pervasives.succ 
> __ocaml_prof_cnt_xcaml_session_.(5); method getvar varname = ....

This is a known bug in 3.06 (PR#1464).  You can get a patch at
< http://caml.inria.fr/patches/pr1464-patch.txt >.

